sentences: Snapp served in the Army Air Forces in World War II; he married his wife Janice in 1942.
On June 26, 1985 he was ejected from a game at the Jack Russell Stadium for playing "Three Blind Mice" in response to what he thought was a bad call from the umpire, Kevin O'Connor.
National Public Radio interview with Snapp's widow Janice Snapp, September 9, 2003

sentences: Wilbur Snapp (August 5, 1920 – September 6, 2003) was a self-taught American musician who was the stadium organist for the Clearwater Phillies, a minor-league baseball team, and for the Philadelphia Phillies in spring training, over a period of 20 years.
